---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../site';
const updated = '8 June 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Legal and privacy"
  description="Privacy and legal information for calibratedideas.com. No analytics, no tracking, no cookies set by this site."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-12">
    <p class="label-mark">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl sm:text-5xl">Legal and privacy</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-[var(--fg-soft)]">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <div class="prose-cal mt-10 max-w-[var(--container-prose)]">
      <h2>Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        This is a static website. It sets no cookies, runs no analytics, and collects no personal
        data about visitors. There are no tracking scripts and no third-party advertising.
      </p>

      <h2>Hosting and server logs</h2>
      <p>
        The site is hosted on shared hosting. As with most web hosting, the host may keep standard
        technical server logs (for example IP addresses and requested pages) for security and
        operational purposes. These logs are handled by the hosting provider under their own terms
        and their own privacy policy.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact by email</h2>
      <p>
        If you email <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>, your message and email
        address are used only to read and reply. They are not added to any mailing list and are not
        shared with anyone else.
      </p>

      <h2>External links</h2>
      <p>
        This site links to projects and services hosted elsewhere (for example the App Store and
        the project websites listed under Projects). Those sites have their own privacy practices,
        which this notice does not cover.
      </p>

      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        Under UK data protection law you have rights over any personal data held about you. As this
        site collects none beyond an email you choose to send, there is little to exercise those
        rights against; even so, you are welcome to contact me with any question at
        <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>This notice may be updated if the site changes. The date above shows the latest version.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
